cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the security of cryptosystems based on the Ring-LWE problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the learning with errors problem, which is related to coding theory and information theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the attack on Ring-LWE. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents an algorithmic attack on Ring-LWE. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the soundness of the Ring-LWE problem.
